## Certification Studies Summary
	Today's studies for the CompTIA A+ exam covered the different storage management technologies including RAID, NAS, and ISCSI. Knowing the importance
  of different storage methodologies is great for determining which one is best for your organization. RAID, or Redundant Array of Independent Disks,
  allows for data to be stored over multiple drives in a way that, should one drive fail, not all data is lost. That does not, however, mean RAID is a
  backup. It is not! There is also NAS, Network Attached Storage, which provides a centralized storage drive that can be accessed across a network.
  I've frequently seen NASs being recommended as a project for Home Labbers since it is relatively simple to set up and configure while allowing 
  shared storage for all connected devices.
